<br>
In order of preference, the FF games I have played:<br>
FF3(VI) - Best story and plot ever, and good graphics for it's time. Got me hooked on RPG's, never looked back.<br>
FF7 - Awe-inspiring graphics, nice story, very customizable system, slightly lacking in the magic department, lack of really touching moments (Aeris getting killed ranks pretty dang high though)<br>
FF2(IV) - I might have had this higher if I had played it sooner, but I didn't play it until after FF7, and never got around to finishing it. Still great.<br>
FF8 - Great graphics, good plot (although a horrible main character), horrible system, contains a few of the most touching FF moments ever<br>
FF9 - Horrible characters (I am playing a MONKEY?! The princess wants to be &quot;normal&quot;, so she takes the name &quot;Dagger&quot;?!), not a very good plot, decent system. SUCH a disappointment.<br>
<br>
FFX has not yet hit the European shelves ... I am counting days. <br>
<br>
I think one of the reasons everyone loves FF3(VI) is because it didn't have a main character. Everyone was free to form their own party, and all the characters had real DEPTH, despite the fact that they were many, and the game was short compared to the newer games. Everyone could pick their own favourite character and develop him/her. You weren't forced upon such bad characters as in 8 and 9. I really wish they would make another FF like that. In FF3(VI), I'd take Phoenix Cave in World of Ruin asap, far earlier when you were supposed to, because I wanted Locke back! Just hate the fact that his personal picture always looked like a sissy.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=nenjindarkeyes>Nenjin Darkeyes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/9/02 4:17:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=7092.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Why was FF3 one of the most popular?<br>
Couple things IMO.<br>
<br>
Yes there was no &quot;main character&quot;. Everyone gets their own piece of the game. But you could also rename all your characters, which in itself isnt big, but like you said, lately you get a specific character, name, abilities, everything. And I really really hate that, considering almost all FF have left you the option to make your chars whatever you want. <br>
<br>
GOOD character backgrounds, which is synonomous with plot and story line, by far my biggest gripe. None of the recent FFs have gripped me with the story lines, and certainly not the characters. I really dont know how to describe whats change, the plots just seem.....flat, there isnt enough fleshing out of the story. Like in FF8, 3/4 of the game you find out the boss is actually some evil chick from the future...ooohhhh, that must have taken a lunch break to cook up. Bah, done ranting.<br>
